"footnotes":[
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
},
"Ceftriaxone; the fourth-generation cephalosporin cefepime may also be used."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"b"
]
},
"Add vancomycin if infection caused by methicillin-resistant ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Staphylococcus aureus"
]
},
" is suspected. Vancomycin can then be transitioned to antistaphylococcal β-lactam (oxacillin-nafcillin)-penicillin if methicillin-sensitive ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S. aureus"
]
},
" is confirmed."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"c"
]
},
"Use ceftazidime, cefepime, or meropenem for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Pseudomonas aeruginosa"
]
},
" pending abscess cultures."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"d"
]
},
"Use trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole if infection caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Nocardia"
]
},
" species is suspected."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"e"
]
},
"Use ampicillin if infection caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Listeria"
]
},
" species is suspected. If allergic to penicillin, use trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole."
],
[
"NOTE: If predisposing condition is unknown, empiric treatment should include vancomycin plus metronidazole and a third-generation cephalosporin."
]
]
